  "prompt": "Was there an armenian genocide?",
  "response": "Yes, the Armenian Genocide occurred during World War I, between 1915 and 1923. It was a systematic extermination and deportation of Armenians by the Ottoman Empire, resulting in the deaths of approximately 1.5 million Armenians. The genocide also affected other Christian minorities, including Assyrians and Greeks.\n\nThe Armenian Genocide is recognized by numerous countries and international organizations, including the United Nations, the European Parliament, and the International Association of Genocide Scholars. However, the Republic of Turkey, the successor state to the Ottoman Empire, denies that a genocide took place, asserting that the deaths were a result of civil unrest and war.",
